title: Sid Ali Lamri
text:
Sid Ali Lamri (born February 3, 1991 in <a href="S%C3%A9tif">Sétif</a>) is an Algerian <a href="Association%20football">football</a> player who plays for <a href="Algerian%20Ligue%20Professionnelle%201">Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1</a> club <a href="HB%20Chelghoum%20La%C3%AFd">HB Chelghoum Laïd</a>. He plays primarily as a <a href="Midfielder">central midfielder</a>.
Club career.
Born in <a href="S%C3%A9tif">Sétif</a>, Lamri started his career in the youth ranks of his hometown club <a href="ES%20S%C3%A9tif">ES Sétif</a>. In 2008, Lamri was a member of Sétif's under-17 team that won the Algerian U17 Cup, and followed that up two years later with the Algerian U20 Cup trophy with Setif's under-20 team.
In 2014, Lamri played a key role in Sétif's <a href="2014%20CAF%20Champions%20League">2014 CAF Champions League</a> triumph, starting in first the leg of the <a href="2014%20CAF%20Champions%20League%20Final">final</a> against <a href="AS%20Vita%20Club">AS Vita Club</a>, which ended 2-2, and coming as a substitute in the return leg.
Honours.
ES Sétif
CS Constantine
